Whereas since 1991, National Nurses Week is celebrated annually from May 6, also known as National
			 Recognition Day for Nurses, through May 12, the birthday of Florence
			 Nightingale, the founder of modern nursing;

Whereas nurses are experienced researchers, and their work encompasses a wide scope of scientific
			 inquiry including clinical research, health systems and outcomes research,
			 and nursing education research;
